{
  "doc_id": "53564",
  "text": "Because, in this work, the motion-copying system employs a ball screw as the slave, forces estimated by the conventional disturbance observer are affected by friction. The elimination of friction can improve the force sensing and control performance. In this paper, our friction compensation method is motivated by the dithering technique [CITATION_1] because our aim is to achieve the friction compensation with a simple implementation. Dithering is a technique defined by the addition of a signal with an appropriate frequency and amplitude to the desired reference signal. The effect of the dither signal is known as the ability to smooth the discontinuity of friction. Therefore, by using dithering method, we do not consider the friction model in our paper.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "31921404"
  },
  "citation_spans": [
